{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9d929b9a89dcf33c","input":{"filename":"release-notes-action-report.md","title":"Prioritized Action Report – Release Notes Drafter","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report – Release Notes Drafter (≤500 words)\n\n**Evidence**: Derived from `analyze_records` output (3 records, risk/opportunity scores).\n\n## 1. Urgent – **Record 13‑A**\n- **Title**: Release notes drafter priority case\n- **Owner**: Product Marketing\n- **Status**: urgent\n- **Impact**: 46,121 (high)\n- **Risk Score**: 9 (high)\n- **Opportunity Score**: 6.6\n- **Summary**: Core capability to turn merged changes into customer‑facing release notes.\n\n**Recommended Action**:\n- Allocate immediate engineering and PM resources to complete pending merge.\n- Conduct a quick validation sprint (≤1 day) to ensure output format matches branding guidelines.\n- Prepare a communication draft for next release cycle.\n\n## 2. Blocked – **Record 13‑C**\n- **Title**: Release notes drafter blocked follow‑up\n- **Owner**: Product Marketing\n- **Status**: blocked\n- **Impact**: 20,743\n- **Risk Score**: 6 (moderate)\n- **Opportunity Score**: 2.1\n- **Summary**: Work halted due to cross‑functional coordination needed.\n\n**Recommended Action**:\n- Identify the blocking dependency (e.g., data pipeline, design sign‑off).\n- Schedule a cross‑team sync (30 min) with the identified stakeholders.\n- Define a concrete unblock milestone and assign an owner.\n\n## 3. In Review – **Record 13‑B**\n- **Title**: Release notes drafter routine queue item\n- **Owner**: Product Marketing\n- **Status**: in_review\n- **Impact**: 10,469\n- **Risk Score**: 2 (low)\n- **Opportunity Score**: 1.0\n- **Summary**: Lower‑risk operational item.\n\n**Recommended Action**:\n- Continue current review process; no additional resources required.\n- Capture any findings as lessons learned for future prioritization.\n\n## Overall Prioritization Logic\n1. **Risk‑adjusted impact** (impact × risk) → 13‑A (≈ 415k), 13‑C (≈ 124k), 13‑B (≈ 21k).\n2. **Status urgency** elevates 13‑A and 13‑C.\n3. **Opportunity** adds secondary weight, favoring 13‑A.\n\n## Next Steps\n- **Immediate**: Kick‑off sprint for 13‑A (within 24 h).\n- **Week 1**: Resolve block for 13‑C via stakeholder meeting.\n- **Ongoing**: Complete review of 13‑B; document outcomes.\n\n*Assumptions*: Scores reflect current business context; no hidden dependencies beyond those noted. All actions are internal and non‑public.\n\n*Prepared by*: Release notes drafter agent (ID 13‑release‑notes‑drafter)."},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:10:33.258Z"}}
